<div id="ta194_85" class="block iDevice_content">
<div class="dentro_contenidos" style="display: block;" id="pagina_1">
<p>The task consists of <b>completing a series of sentences</b> in order to show that students can understand details and specific information.</p>
<p>Students are required to complete 10 sentences from a spoken text with the information heard on the recording.</p>
<p>Tips:</p>
<ul>
<li>First, read the sentences carefully and think about the type of information you will need to fill the space.</li>
<li>Think about the type of word that will probably fill the gap (a noun, an adjective, etc). Most of the times you will need between one and three words.</li>
<li>Write the words you actually hear.</li>
<li>Be careful to choose the right information, other ideas may be mentioned.</li>
<li>Read the sentence at the end to make sure the words fit grammatically.</li>
<li>Answer every question even if you are not sure.</li>
</ul>
</div>
